main event: A large silver balloon-shaped object was observed over Vero Beach, Florida for approximately 4 minutes on October 17, 1965.
interesting points: Witnesses reported an unexplained power shortage leading to the investigation,Fragments of the balloon were found on power lines,The object was officially concluded to be a balloon,Power company men were alerted due to the power loss,There is physical evidence of the sighting with fragments collected from the site.
witness description: Civilian observers and power company personnel
